---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import PhilosophyCallout from '../../components/docs/PhilosophyCallout.astro';
import ButtonShowcase from '../../components/cleo/ButtonShowcase.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Buttons" description="Cleo button components">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Buttons</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">Slate reads as calm authority. Cream reads as warmth. Together: I know what I'm doing and I care about you.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="wide-band">
    <ButtonShowcase />
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Specifications</h2>
    <table class="token-table">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Primary</strong></td>
          <td>Slate background (<code>#2E4057</code>), cream text (<code>#F5EBD6</code>). Default important action — e.g. “Sign note”.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Amber CTA</strong></td>
          <td>Amber background (<code>#D4841A</code>), cream text. The single most important action on the page — e.g. “Sign and submit”. Use once per screen.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Ghost</strong></td>
          <td>Transparent fill, 0.5px slate border, slate text. Secondary actions that step back — e.g. “Edit draft”.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Disabled</strong></td>
          <td>45% opacity. Same dimensions as primary. No hover or press feedback.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Shared specs</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Font: DM Sans, medium (500), 17px</li>
      <li>Padding: 10px × 24px</li>
      <li>Border radius: 8px</li>
      <li>Press: scale(0.98), 150ms ease-out</li>
      <li>Hover: primary → midnight; ghost → light slate tint; amber → slight brighten</li>
    </ul>

    <PhilosophyCallout>
      <p>Secondary actions step back so the interface never competes with the therapist's attention — Frame 3 skepticism requires the UI to prove restraint before asking for trust.</p>
    </PhilosophyCallout>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
